{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91d60797-9119-4267-9bdd-f843a28a5d5f","content":"Here's the equivalent command using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) arguments passed after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Mapping summary:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n| `--filter` | stays before `--` (understood by `dotnet test`) |\n\n**Prerequisites** — your test project needs:\n- `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` in the csproj (or `Directory.Build.props`)\n- Package references for `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` / `HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2bae601c-ee95-4aba-b51e-de70dd94b288","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage package)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith .NET 8 and MTP, `dotnet test` should work with the `--` separator to pass MTP-specific arguments, though I need to verify the exact integration level available in .NET 8 versus .NET 9+.\n\nFor .NET 8 with MTP, the project needs to opt in via `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` or `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>`, then you can run something like `dotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura --crashdump --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m`. Now I'm thinking through how code coverage specifically works with MTP. The `--filter` parameter can be placed either before or after the `--` separator since both `dotnet test` and MTP understand it in either position.","outputTokens":1078,"requestId":"5C43:33128B:9CE11:C61E5:69F54AA7"},"id":"04d3a26f-e404-4fd9-8cbc-45a95c340544","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:53:22.757Z","parentId":"38c9935f-af41-4572-a334-f43f9ab4ac50"}
